dcterms:creator: D. Greenberg
M. Nonnenmacher
J. Macke
dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset generated from a two-moon simulator, which produces observations based on parameters drawn from a uniform distribution. The dataset is used for likelihood-free inference.
dcterms:title: Two-moon model

dcterms:creator: D. T. Gillespie
dcterms:description: A dataset generated from the Lotka-Volterra model, which describes the dynamics of predator-prey interactions using a stochastic Markov jump process. The dataset includes time series data of predator and prey populations.
dcterms:title: Lotka-Volterra model

dcterms:creator: A. Y. Shestopaloff
R. M. Neal
dcterms:description: A dataset generated from the M/G/1 queue model, which describes the processing of jobs by a single server. The dataset includes statistics on job inter-arrival and service times.
dcterms:title: M/G/1 queue model
